This paper deals with the ResNet model for visual recognition, which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture for residual networks, which involves optimizing the network's memory use and training time, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
